Heart is the fullest. 💛Spending a few days at @selenalakehouse with the Stay Here team as we dream and scheme for next year. Today is officially Stay Here’s two year anniversary - and wow what a two years it’s been. We’ve branded and designed three beautiful properties and one wellness pop up over the last two years and are just putting the finishing touches on our biggest project to date- a nine suite inn we’ve dubbed Hotel Julie- that we are filming a TV show about. (No big deal haha!) This tiny team is working on the plans to expand Hotel Julie into a cafe + more suites alongside a few other juicy consults and projects that we can’t wait to share more about. We are collectively working on a massive rebrand- embracing our new path in wellness and leaning more into hosted retreats. I can’t thank my incredible team enough for being on this journey with me, this is only the beginning. #youshouldstayhere

Because one @437 shoot wasn’t enough 😉haha. Just trying to remember to breaaathe. Looking forward to taking a little mid day break tomorrow to do some pilates at @sparkpilates followed by an assisted @stretchlabtoronto_downtown stretch! It’s been a looot of head down concentrated -don’t-even-stop-to-eat-focused deep work lately trying to get as much done before the holidays as possible. Sometimes the best route is to actually schedule in some time to slow down. Where my google calendar people at!?? (Also… this gal mighhhhhht be planning a little post holiday vacation… anyone have any Costa Rica reccos!??)🌱 img: @ryngrg

It’s when you feel like you “don’t have time”…that you have to make the time. Living a healthy, active lifestyle as a busy entrepreneur comes down to discipline. Discipline with your scheduling. Discipline with yourself. When you’re incredibly busy it can be really hard “justify” spending your lunch hour doing yoga.. but here’s the thing.. by prioritizing your wellness and mental health you’re actually able to bring your best self to work. I feel so lucky to have @goodspace.to around the corner from me. Environment absolutely has the ability to affect our moods and mental health. Goodspace is bright, airy, relaxing, and always smells so. freaking. good. The instructors are all so inspiring and I ALWAYS leave the studio feeling better than when I walked in. If you want to give the studio a shot you can save 10% off a single or 6 pack class using my code: MOVEWITHAUTUMN. 🧘🏼‍♀️

I have been thinking a lot about my over all fitness and physique goals and how I can create a fitness schedule that better matches my goals.
One of my goals has been to do some glute focused workouts that primarily isolate the glute muscles and are less quad dominant. Building those booty muscles baby haha! 🍑🍑I have been trying to get into a good routine of going to @staygoldtoronto Buns of Gold” class on Sundays. (Looks like they have a booty focused class Wed nights too!) 

Additionally I mentioned flexibility is a major goal of mine and trying to introduce more “feminine energy” and flow into my weekly routines. For a really long time all the workouts I have done have been hard, fast, metal music type workouts haha. Living in my masculine. Looking ahead I want to integrate some more slower paced, intentional, connective workouts- like @sparkpilates, @goodspace.to and @stretchlabtoronto_downtown. (Annnd maybe some dance 😏) Also becoming more consistent with weekly plunges at either @othership, @unboundedwell or in the good old fashioned lake haha. Although I will say I did my first real lake plunge recently and it’s a bit less comfortable than the plunges I’ve done in the past hahaha. I’ll have to toughen up. 😘

It’s wild that there was a time when I had no workout regime at all- on Sundays I book all my upcoming classes and it’s one of my favourite rituals each week. ☀️ happy Sunday!!

Needed a moment for this dress….Ryan’s alright too.😏😏😏 a lil holiday romance if you will. 🎄 This was an unexpected little evolution - we met at a cold plunge this summer annnnnd our let’s just be friends turned into let’s be more than just friends.🤪Excited to be entering 2023 with a partner in crime. If ya don’t know, now ya know.
Double the buns of gold. A new sunday tradition. 🏆 @staygoldtoronto

Trimming the tree (literally 😂 ✂️) 🎄 🙈 - also Ryan may have suffered some slight PTSD from having to film ANOTHER tree time lapse( he just spent the last month filming the Dior tree Timelapse at the Distillery District .. I’ll you decide who’s is more impressive hahaha) RyAut tree > Dior tree. 😉🎄

I’m sure I’m not the only one starting to reflect on 2022 while looking ahead to 2023. 

Over the last few years movement has become a really big pillar in my life. I’ve (imperfectly) completed the 75 hard challenge three times now and every time I learn more about myself and grow inside and out. 

Upon completing the last challenge I’ve been really contemplating how I want to push myself moving into the new year. I’ve defined that some of my major fitness goals are to work on my flexibility, incorporate some slower controlled workouts into my routine, lean into embracing my feminine energy and move my body in a way that flows. I think it’s important to try new things and have new experiences to broaden my perspective. 

Reformer based classical Pilates is something new I’ve been exploring lead by the incredibly talented Dervola from @sparkpilates. Through our first few sessions I’ve started to really learn how to better connect my mind with my muscles.

She’s constantly inspiring me to be more aware of my posture- lengthening me and assisting me in stretching. I think 2023 in general is about stretching further, digging deeper, being more intentional and connecting on a deeper level. ⚡️

Sitting by the fire at @anupaya with @ryngrg thinking about how grateful I am to hit reset. I get pretty reflective every new year but this year is extra special as I’m going through a rebrand for my company. @you.should.stay.here has grown so much in the short two years we’ve been around and this next evolution is really just connecting all the dots to create something so much deeper, soulful and more aligned. ⚪️

This weekend was Ryan and I’s first real work collaboration together - shooting a couple different photo and video collections. Honestly- I’ve always dreamed about this. Having someone to run away to cabins with, explore, create and spend time in nature with..(I didn’t necessarily dream about cold plunging at night in a frozen river (twice…. I am currently stalling haha)…but alas).

I’m really excited about the content we have been creating together and we’re very excited to be offering up new cinematic photo and video packages for short term rental owners. Drop me a DM if you’d like more info- we’d love to see and share your space.
Cabin fever. 🌲 @ryngrg

Who knew frozen water would have such a big impact on my life? 🧊

Everything started with the first 75 hard- which then lead me on a path of digging deeper, expanding, connecting, growing. (Which would you guys believe me if I said is coming up on my two year anniversary of!??? I did the first challenge March 1st, 2021 🤯)

Shortly into my first challenge I was approached by Inward breath to be a part of their beta testing group.. testing breath work tracks and joining monthly zoom calls during the pandemic. Inward evolved into what we all know as Othership. Othership has been a constant source of inspiration for me.. a new staple in my weekly routine. A way to de stress. Let go. Recalibrate. Connect. Find love..(I met @ryngrg at a cold plunge, how fitting 😏).

Today is day 19/31 of @othership’s #PlayItCool challenge. With newly released cold plunge tracks each day of the challenge it’s been an incredible journey finding a new place to dip each day. From stormy lakes dips ten minutes before midnight, to couples classes at the ship, to finding ways wherever we go (like this boujee dip five star dip at @shinolahotel in Detroit).. where there’s a will, there’s way. It’s been challenging and has really proved to me once again then when you commit to something full heartedly- real transformation can occur. 🛸

Tap the link in my bio to give it a shot. 📷: @ryngrg

A little dump of life lately!

Life’s been willddd. My camera roll is literally just full of progress photos of furniture, art and construction- but those are all things I can’t share yet- so here’s some snippets of life in between. 

@ryngrg and I have been trying to pack in some fun life things before heading into this crazy shoot schedule. The past month has been filled with lots of cold water haha.. (I successfully completed 31 days of cold plunging in a row… Ryan is on day 57 in a row… I decided to take a little break haha but will be joining him periodically through the rest of his 100 days). We celebrated 1 year of @othership last week on the beach with friends and fire and it was perfect. We have only seen sun 3 or so times since starting to dip and we were greeted with the most stunning sunrise. It was really special. 

We took a trip to Deep river and stayed at a beautiful cabin called @anupaya. We shot our first collections together there- coming soon! We are backlogged on editing haha. 
We took a trip to Detroit- had an incredible stay at @shinolahotel. We explored- ate allll the coney dogs and pizza and ice cream. (Wellness is all about balance amirite?!)
We toured out to Hamilton to check out a new coffee shop.. went to Niagara falls to test drive a really cool new form of light and sound therapy- excited to share more as one of my friends launches her company. 
January saw lots of snuggles with @iamziggysmallz, vintage shopping, brunch with friends and a little extra self care in the form of facials at @tightclinic- which I 10/10 recommend Maria is incredible. 

February is going to be challenging and exciting. It’s going to be emotionally charged and full of creative energy. Excited to be on the other side feeling proud, realigned and almost to the other side of the biggest project I’ve ever done. ⚡️Remembering to breathe, take it one day at a time and focus on all of the incredible hard work that has happened over the past year to get to this point. I got this, you got this, we got this.
Man crush Monday 😏😏😏. Love snapping pics of this cutie. Too many good memories from our Detroit trip. ❤️

33 baby. ☀️

My thirties so far have been some of the hardest/most incredible/most transformative years of my life so far. 

I’ve quite literally quantum leaped from 30-33 and am living a new reality that I created for myself.. and I’m just getting started. I’m in the final stages of wrapping up the biggest project I’ve ever undertaken and I am leaning in to a full spectrum of emotions. I feel equal parts exhausted and exhilarated. I feel a major sense of accomplishment and pride. I feel excited and curious about how this new chapter will unfold. 

The other side wrapping up this project looks like ease. It looks like hitting reset. It looks like expansion. It looks like digging into all the lessons I’ve learned and turning them into something even better. It looks like stepping into a new level of consciousness, reconnecting with myself, gaining clarity, and living with unbounded creativity and love. ❤️

I am taking today as a day of reflection. 🧘🏼‍♀️When it feels like there is too much to do and there is no time for yourself and you’ve been pushing for so long—that’s exactly when you need to take a step back. Instead of pushing until I’m completely burnt out and bedridden.. I am taking time now. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This past year and a half has been filled with so.much.growth—in so many areas. So many “firsts”. I’ve learned about what I love to do, what I don’t love to do, areas where I excel and areas where I need to empower someone else to thrive in their creative genius.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Overall I learned that my routines and my wellness rituals need to come before anything else. That whatever I am doing, wherever I am working- I need to first prioritize my own mental health, movement and spirituality. That I need to prioritize rest. That I need to spend time actually “logging off”. That the world will still operate without me being available at any given second. That I’m actually kind of a homebody.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I am so grateful to be starting a new chapter. For this breath of fresh air to redesign my lifestyle and schedule in a way that promotes the most authentic, vibrant, passionately creative version of me. To lean into more of what I love, to be curious, to continue expanding. As one of my coaches mentioned—I need to schedule in some time for magic… and that is exactly where I am going to start.✨
📸: @ryngrg 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Fellow CEOS and biz owners- how do you feel about your weekly schedules and routines? Do you prioritize your wellness? Do you save space for magic?

My morning routine is the best part of my day. It’s the way that I take control of my mindset and start the day with an open heart. 🤍

Or should I say, OUR morning routine because @ryngrg and I have synced up morning routines together and it’s the most nourishing, connective, grounding little pocket of our days that we truly both look forward to every day. Our morning routine involves some healthy concoctions, vitamins and supplements, movement, journalling and sharing, connection, incense, stretching, and breathwork. Every morning we do breathwork before we journal to sink deeper into everything we are grateful for. 

We filmed this little breathwork sequence at @anupaya earlier this year to share a little BTS for anyone who hasn’t tried breathwork. This is a track from the @othership.app (this one’s called Energy Level Up). I can’t begin to express how much I love Othership and how much it’s impacted my life. (Heck, Ryan and I met at a Sunrise social where Othership lead the breathwork ;). Incorporating breathing into our daily routine has allowed us to regulate our nervous systems and increase our energy. ⚡️It’s the best way to start each morning, I promise. If you want to give it a shot there’s a link in my bio (Othership App).. Another one of my personal favourite tracks is “Creativity” by Devon and Ryan’s fav track is  Ultra Minimal by Harry. (the longer the breath hold the better!!) Give it a go and let us know what you think!!

It lives up to the hype. @kellywearstler is the GOAT. We are having the most incredible stay at @properhotels @santamonicaproper ❤️‍🔥 #youshouldstayhere

Rediscovering parts of yourself that you temporarily left behind is beautiful. I honestly forgot what @you.should.stay.here meant to me. Stay here is a design firm- yes.. but we are also an experience and travel brand. We share the best places to stay because we come ALIVE at the thought of staying in a thoughtfully designed space. We love capturing interesting spaces and sharing them a community that values investing in experiences. We design gorgeous spaces because of how much gorgeous intentional spaces impact us. We have been profiling places to stay for close ten years now and I still get the same little butterflies opening the hotel room door whether I’m staying at a tiny cabin on a lake, or at the Proper Hotel in Santa Monica. (And now I get to play a part of CREATING those feelings and memories for other people).

We pour over creating itineraries and having meaningful experiences. We fully appreciate the effort that goes into unique and interesting design, or finding the perfect vintage piece. Design truly is therapy and the environment you surround yourself with affects your wellbeing. 

Staying at the @santamonicaproper @properhotels was more than a hotel stay for me. This was affirmation that I am on the right path. That I am exactly where I need to be. Thank you @kellywearstler for sharing your gift with the world. #youshouldstayhere 📷 : @ryngrg
Staying properly hydrated. 💧 @properhotels @santamonicaproper

We have been doing our best to stick to our routines this trip. I would say this is the first trip I’ve ever went on in my adult life that has an overarching wellness theme. We aren’t drinking. We are getting up and prioritizing breathwork and movement and journalling. We are eating nutritiously (with a few donuts thrown in for good measure haha). We have scheduled a handful of wellness related activities (breathwork, sauna cold plunge, the light and sound installation, a wellness event!) It feels like a whole new way of life (because it truly is). One thing that we both noticed is that the gym at the Proper was packed at 5am. In both of our experience the gym is usually a ghost town in the morning at hotels. It kind of just further compounded our hypothesis on the type of person who would stay at the Proper. Someone who cares about and is willing to invest in great design. Someone who cares about their health and body. Someone who has discipline on vacation. Someone who values sustainability. To be honest- our stay at the Proper was the best hotel experience I have ever had and I’ve been profiling hotels for close to ten years. The design and service were both exceptional. The level of detail and thoughtfulness were unmatched. I feel so expanded by this experience and I am so grateful that we were able to stay here. @properhotels  @santamonicaproper #youshouldstayhere #stayhereusa #stayhereLA #stayheresantamonica

What frequency are you choosing to be in today? Everything you’re doing is an expression of your consciousness. 🦋

I gotta say- doing quantum mindset coaching with your partner might be my biggest relationship hack haha. We had a dope group session while on vacation and it really just allowed us to tap in. Todays focus is: being completely present. No work. Allowing for a childlike sense of wonder (we are trying surfing for the first time!!). Coming in to the day with a feelings first point of view. Today will feel expansive, effortless, connected. How about you? 

Gorgeous portraits by my incredibly talented boyfriend 📷 @ryngrg

The sunlight in LA though. ☀️🥹 @ryngrg and I have been having the best vacation ever. This is the first time I’ve ever travelled and have not been drinking alcohol. Instead of drinking we’ve been filling our cup with all the wellness activities. It’s been so beautiful taking our little wellness routines on the road. Something new that I am starting to incorporate into my routines is dry brushing and body gua sha. (Also face Gua sha of course!) I love @stephflockhart’s tutorials. As I move into this next season (The season of Autumn! 🍂) I am truly making a commitment to slow down. 75 slow is coming soon and these mind body connective activities will be a priority. 🤍 📷: @ryngrg

*starts googling “apartments for rent in LA.”

How epic is this shot @ryngrg captured at Dumes Point in Malibu? It’s been so incredible seeing Ryan in his element. (Is this also maybe my element??) lol. The waffle fit is also fire, from @pokolokoltd 🤍

I’ve spent the better half of the last two days in bed with the wooooorst cold. I had all these grand ambitions to have a “working vacation”.. (what even is that? Why did I plan that? Lol) I had some business things I wanted to work on surrounded by all the inspo in LA..all while, exploring and shooting properties from dawn to dusk.. aka.. not possible. 

A great reminder that I actually needed a vacation, not to work more. 

Feeling immensely grateful for this man right here. He is so kind, thoughtful and loving and has been taking the best care of me. 🥹 Despite not having much time to fully relax- we have been having an absolute blast exploring and creating together. We know this is truly just the beginning and the thought of all the adventures in our future makes my heart full. I love you Ryan. ❤️‍🔥 📷: @ryngrg

Ryan and I have been all over the map as of late— before we took our trip to LA we spent a few days surrounded by nature at a gorgeous tiny cabin @sunsetviewtinycabin in Restoule Ontario shooting for @you.should.stay.here. This unique couples getaway is the most charming oasis with everything you need for a cozy stay. Nestled right on Lake Restoule- the sunsets are unmatched. We enjoyed spending time out on the water in kayaks, fires at night with our own private fire pit, and cooking outside in the outdoor kitchen. There was a natural running spring nearby where we took daily trips to stock up our water supply and we visited the local bee farm for honey and treats. The tiny cabin even had an ice plunge available for use and an outdoor movie projector. We loved shooting this space and definitely recommend planning a trip! 📹: @ryngrg

Whether you’re aware of it or not, your every day life is a series of habits and routines. Roughly 45% of your day is spent on “autopilot”. There’s lots of reasons for this rooted in our biology and psychology. Its estimated that we have 60,000 thoughts a day and make up to 35,000 decisions. Our brains go on autopilot in order to work efficiently and conserve energy. 

My routines used to involve hitting the snooze button multiple times, and barely making it out the door on time. After long, exhausting workdays, I'd come home, faced with the daunting question: "What should I make for dinner?"

Living in a state of hustle all day long and not properly nourishing my body during the day- by the time I got home I would be VERY hungry and opt for anything that was going to be the FASTEST option. The quickest option was rarely the most nourishing or healthy option and a lot of times was also the most expensive option (hello Uber eats). I'd end up feeling both physically and financially drained.

Fast forward to today, and I've finally found a way to navigate my life effectively. For me, planning is everything. I meticulously schedule my week, taking into account my commitments and even where I am in my cycle. I'm constantly fine-tuning these routines to fit my lifestyle better.

The thing to note here is that by developing and following through with systems, I have been able to build trust with myself. It doesn't mean I'm perfect and I’m not trying to be, there are lots of days when I deviate from these routines. They aren’t meant to feel restrictive or controlling. What I've realized is that without a plan, I struggle to focus. Having a structured framework is a safety net that supports me on my off days.

Over time, I've developed systems for meal prepping, weekly planning, morning and evening routines, and Sunday rituals. I'm sharing all my templates, advice, and resources on the @designedbyether portal to help others implement support systems that work for them. It's not about guilt or shame when you can't stick to these tasks; it's about providing yourself with the support you need to thrive in your unique way. #75slowchallenge

Coming from a marketing background into the world of interior design—starting with a strategy was just a no brainer for me. Especially when it comes to hospitality based or commercial projects. Your brand strategy acts as the road map for every business (and aesthetic) decision you will make for your project. It acts as the guidelines and the north star so that you can make decisions with conviction —and also make decisions rooted in reason.

Let’s take Hotel Julie for example.

Much like ANY project- the strategy leads the way— and had the strategy for Hotel Julie been to attract millennials hosting bachelorette parties, or host athletes passing through the town on their way to a tournament—the design, language, aesthetics would all be wildly different.

For Hotel Julie- we leaned into what was already existing—a gorgeous town with a rich theatrical culture. Knowing that our dream guest was someone who enjoyed theatre- all of our decisions laddered up to that insight. The sconces behind the bars emulate the ruffle on a Shakespearean collar. The brass hardware in the kitchen felt rich, luxe, and grand (a few of our brand tone words).. The velvet on the bar stools is reminiscent of theater curtains. The calacatta viola is MOODY and brings DRAMA, the classic checkerboard carpet, the vintage theatre books. Every single inch of this space was designed in line with our strategy.

Crafting the Resonance brand was about diving into the hearts and psyches of our audience, transcending demographics. We aimed for a brand that offers hope to both those familiar with alternate healing and those seeking a new path.

For those feeling defeated after trying traditional methods, we found our balance between the ethereal and the familiar.

Using a monospace font for its reliability, our typography laid the foundation for the Resonance brand. Inspired by vintage textbooks, we added an academic touch for a feel of dependability and familiarity. Referencing rocks and minerals added an earthly duality.

Creating a sanctuary as our foundation then paved the way for contrast and tension with otherworldly elements. The color palette mirrors the chakra system, evoking warmth and modernity in equal measure. Paired with a custom logomark and infographic illustrations, the design exudes calm, making Resonance feel both compelling and established.
